  "source": "[\\function:from{A}:to{B}]\nDescribes: f(x__) ::= y_\nwhen: A, B is \\set\nspecifies:\n. x__ \"in\" A\n. y_ \"in\" B\nDocumented:\n. called: \"function from $A?$ to $B?$\"\n. written: \"f? \\colon A? \\to B?\"\n. description: \"A function $f \\colon A \\to B$ assigns to each $a \\in A$ a unique value $f(a) \\in B$. Here $A$ is the domain and $B$ the codomain of $f$. As a relation it is the set of pairs $(a, f(a))$.\"\nId: \"26a5755e-e596-46b5-8828-3fc5a39da156\"",
